problem_text: If people own a large desktop monitor at their home, then they work regularly and often at home. All people who have a fully stocked and impressive home office are people who own a large desktop monitor at their home. All people who work regularly and often at home spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their homes. All people who work regularly and often at home visit the office supply store regularly. If people spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, then they do not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon. Remy either both goes to bed late and wakes up every day after noon and spends their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, or they do not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon nor spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home.
predicates:
OwnsLargeDesktopMonitor(x) ::: x owns a large desktop monitor at their home.
WorksRegularlyAndOftenAtHome(x) ::: x works regularly and often at home.
HasFullyStockedAndImpressiveHomeOffice(x) ::: x has a fully stocked and impressive home office.
SpendsFreeTimeTidyingAndOrganizing(x) ::: x spends their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home.
VisitsOfficeSupplyStoreRegularly(x) ::: x visits the office supply store regularly.
GoesToBedLate(x) ::: x goes to bed late.
WakesUpEveryDayAfterNoon(x) ::: x wakes up every day after noon.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy visits the office supply store regularly, then Remy has a fully stocked and impressive home office.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy works regularly and often at home, then Remy does not visit the office supply store regularly.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy spends their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, then Remy works regularly and often at home.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy has a fully stocked and impressive home office, then Remy goes to bed late.

Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Remy owns a large desktop monitor at their home and Remy does not spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Remy works regularly and often at home if and only if Remy visits the office supply store regularly.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Remy either owns a large desktop monitor at their home or Remy visits the office supply store regularly.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy works regularly and often at home, then Remy does not go to bed late.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy owns a large desktop monitor at their home, then Remy visits the office supply store regularly.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Remy does not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon, then Remy works regularly and often at home.
